Section 1:
1 L.D. 1341
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 MARINE RESOURCES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 556, L.D. 1341, “Resolve, Directing the
10 Department of Marine Resources to Evaluate How to Effectively Allow 2 Licensed
11 Individuals to Fish for Lobsters or Scallops from a Single Vessel”
12 Amend the resolve by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 1. Operation from single vessel review; lobster fishery. Resolved: That
14 the Department of Marine Resources shall evaluate how 2 individuals who each hold a
15 valid Class I, Class II or Class III lobster and crab fishing license and who are fishing
16 concurrently from the same vessel may fish for or take lobsters from a single vessel without
17 this resulting in increased harvest. In completing its review, the department may consult
18 with and seek input from the Lobster Advisory Council under the Maine Revised Statutes,
19 Title 12, section 6462-A and lobster management policy councils established pursuant to
20 Title 12, section 6447.
21 Sec. 2. Operation from single vessel review; scallop fishery. Resolved: That
22 the Department of Marine Resources shall evaluate how 2 individuals who each hold a
23 scallop dragging license and who are fishing concurrently from the same vessel may fish
24 for or take scallops from a single vessel without this resulting in increased harvest. In
25 completing its review, the department may consult with and seek input from the Scallop
26 Advisory Council under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 12, section 6729-B.
27 Sec. 3. Report. Resolved: That the Department of Marine Resources shall submit
28 a report to the Joint Standing Committee on Marine Resources by March 1, 2026 describing
29 the review process in sections 1 and 2.'
30 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
31 section number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment makes the following changes to the resolve:
Page 1 - 132LR1858(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 556, L.D. 1341
1 1. It adds language to specify that 2 individuals described for the evaluation who are
2 fishing for lobster or scallops from a single vessel must be fishing concurrently from the
3 same vessel;
4 2. It removes the requirement that the Department of Marine Resources convey its
5 findings and recommendations to the Atlantic States Marine Fisheries Commission and
6 also removes the requirement that the department include information on these discussions
7 in its report to the Joint Standing Committee on Marine Resources;
8 3. It changes the reporting date from January 14, 2026 to March 1, 2026; and
9 4. It removes language authorizing the Joint Standing Committee on Marine Resources
10 to report out a bill based on the Department of Marine Resources' report.
1111 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1122 (See attached)
